      • getPropertyCategory

        public static String getPropertyCategory(String property)
        Gets the parent category from a given property string. This method is used in many places by many different consumers. In general, it will check to see if the property contains arguments. If not, then a simple String.substring(int, int) is used along with EXTERNAL_PATH_SEP.

        In the event that a property contains a $d parameter, it will attempt to strip out any embedded methods in the various tokens. For example, if a property of foo/$1.substring(5)/bar/$2.substring(1)/baz is given, the expected recursive categories would be:

        • foo
        • foo/$1
        • foo/$1/bar
        • foo/$1/bar
        • foo/$1/bar/$2
        foo/$1.substring(5)/bar is incorrect as a category.
        Parameters:
        property - the fully qualified property
        Returns:
        the property category; null if there is no category

      • updateMetricsWithAggregateFunctionSupport

        public static void updateMetricsWithAggregateFunctionSupport(Map<String,Map<String,PropertyInfo>> metrics)
        This method adds supported propertyInfo for component metrics with aggregate function ids. API calls with multiple aggregate functions applied to a single metric need this support. Currently this support is added only for Component & Report metrics. This can be easily extended by making the call from the appropriate sub class of: @AMSPropertyProvider.
